The Central Population Administrative System (MERNIS) data base which is available on-line.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.turkstat.gov.tr/PreTablo.do?alt_id=37 |title=::Welcome to Turkish Statistical Institute(TurkStat)'s Web Pages |publisher=TurkStat |date= |accessdate=2014-06-17}}</ref> Birth statistics are updated continually because MERNIS has dynamic structure.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.turkstat.gov.tr/PreTablo.do?tb_id=37&ust_id=11 |title=Turkish Statistical Institute |publisher=Turkstat.gov.tr |date= |accessdate=2014-06-17}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010 Turkey had a crude birth rate of 17.2 per 1000, in 2011 16.7, down from 20.3 in 2001. The total fertility rate (TFR) in 2010 was 2.05 children per woman, in 2011 2.02. The crude birth rate in 2010 ranged from 11.5 in [[Marmara Region|West Marmara]] (TFR 1.52) (11,5;1.55 in 2011), similar to [[Bulgaria]], to 27.9 in [[Southeastern Anatolia Region|Southeast Anatolia]] (TFR 3.53) (27.1;3,42 in 2011), similar to [[Syria]]. Similarly, in 2012, the TFR ranged from 1.43 in [[K\u0131rklareli]], to 4.39 in [[\u015eanl\u0131urfa]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Turkish Statistical Institute (TurkStat) |url=http://www.turkstat.gov.tr/PreHaberBultenleri.do?id=13618 |title=Turkish Statistical Institute Birth Statistics 2012 |publisher=Turkstat.gov.tr |date=2012-08-31 |accessdate=2014-06-17}}</ref> Deaths statistics from MERNIS are available as of 2009. Mortality data prior to 2009 are incomplete.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Population (31.12.)\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Live births\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Deaths\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Natural change\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Crude birth rate (per 1000)\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Crude death (per 1000)\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Natural increase (per 1000)\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Total fertility rate (TFR)\n|-\n| 2001\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,323,341\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 175,137\t\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|