 name=\"tuik2018\">{{cite web|url=http://www.turkstat.gov.tr/HbGetirHTML.do?id=27587 |title=Turkish Statistical Institute |publisher=Turkstat.gov.tr |date= 2018-02-01 |accessdate=2018-04-09}}</ref> According to OECD/World Bank population statistics, from 1990 to 2008 the [[population growth]] in Turkey was 16 million or 29%.<ref name=IEApop2011>[http://www.iea.org/co2highlights/co2Highlights.XLS CO2 Emissions from Fuel Combustion] Population 1971\u20132008 ([http://iea.org/co2highlights/co2highlights.pdf pdf] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120106205757/http://iea.org/co2highlights/co2highlights.pdf |date=2012-01-06 }} pages&nbsp;83\u201385) IEA (OECD/ World Bank) original population ref e.g. in IEA Key World Energy Statistics 2010 page 57</ref>\n\n== Population ==\n[[File:Turkey total fertility rate by province 2014.png|thumb|Turkey Total fertility rate by province (2013).<ref>{{cite web|title=TurkStat|url=http://www.turkstat.gov.tr/PreIstatistikTablo.do?istab_id=1452|publisher=TurkStat|accessdate=2015-03-22|date=2013}}</ref> {{legend|#ff6500|4-5}} {{legend|#ffff00|3-4}} {{legend|#0cff00|2-3}} {{legend|#24e0d9|1.5-2}} {{legend|#3aafe0|1-1.5}}]]\n\n{{Historical populations\n|title       = Historical population<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.turkstat.gov.tr/PreTablo.do?tb_id=39&ust_id=11 |title=Population Statistics And Projections |publisher=Turkstat.gov.tr |date= |accessdate=2014-06-17}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.turkstat.gov.tr/Kitap.do?metod=KitapDetay&KT_ID=11&KITAP_ID=12 |title=Census of Population ; Social and Economic Characteristics of Population, Turkey |publisher=Turkstat.gov.tr |date= |accessdate=2016-04-15}}</ref>|align       = none | cols = 2\n|shading     = off\n|percentages = pagr\n|1927|13648270\n|1935|16158018\n|1940|17820950\n|1945|18790174\n|1950|20947188\n|1955|24064763\n|1960|27754820\n|1965|31391421\n|1970|35605176\n|1975|40347719\n|1980|44736957\n|1985|50664458\n|1990|56473035\n|2000|67803927\n|2010|73722988\n|2015|78