ar to [[Bulgaria]], to 27.9 in [[Southeastern Anatolia Region|Southeast Anatolia]] (TFR 3.53) (27.1;3,42 in 2011), similar to [[Syria]]. Similarly, in 2012, the TFR ranged from 1.43 in [[K\u0131rklareli]], to 4.39 in [[\u015eanl\u0131urfa]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Turkish Statistical Institute (TurkStat) |url=http://www.turkstat.gov.tr/PreHaberBultenleri.do?id=13618 |title=Turkish Statistical Institute Birth Statistics 2012 |publisher=Turkstat.gov.tr |date=2012-08-31 |accessdate=2014-06-17}}</ref> Deaths statistics from MERNIS are available as of 2009. Mortality data prior to 2009 are incomplete.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Population (31.12.)\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Live births\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Deaths\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Natural change\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Crude birth rate (per 1000)\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Crude death (per 1000)\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Natural increase (per 1000)\n! style=\"width:80pt;\"|Total fertility rate (TFR)\n|-\n| 2001\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,323,341\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 175,137\t\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,148,204\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 20.3\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:right; color:blue;\"| 2.37\n|-\n| 2002\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,229,555\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 175,434\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,054,121\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 18.6\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:right; color:blue;\"| 2.17\n|-\n| 2003\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,198,927\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 184,330\t\t\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1,014,597\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 17.9\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 2.09\n|-\n| 2004\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|\n| style=\"t