{"title_page": "Leo Fitz", "text_new": "{{short description|Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. character}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox character\n| color              = #AF181F\n| name               = Leo Fitz\n| series             = {{no italics|[[Marvel Cinematic Universe]]}}\n| image              = Leo Fitz.jpg\n| caption            = Iain De Caestecker as Leo Fitz in a promotional image for [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 4)|season four]]\n| first_minor        = [[Pilot (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Pilot]]\n| creator            = {{plainlist|\n* [[Joss Whedon]]\n* [[Jed Whedon]]\n* [[Maurissa Tancharoen]]\n}}\n| portrayer          = [[Iain De Caestecker]]\n| full_name          = Leopold James Fitz<ref name=\"Identity and Change\">{{Cite episode |title=Identity and Change |episode-link=Identity and Change (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=April 11, 2017 |season=4 |number=17 |quote='''Simmons:''' It's complicated, but I know him, not as the Doctor, but as {{sic|a a}} brilliant, awkward, heroic scientist named Leopold James Fitz.}}</ref>\n| alias              = The Doctor\n| occupation         = Engineer<br />[[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] agent\n| nationality        = Scottish<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ew.com/tv/2017/02/24/spoiler-room-arrow-shield-blacklist/ |title=Spoiler Room: Scoop on 'Arrow,' 'Agents of SHIELD,' 'Blacklist,' more |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=24 February 2017 |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190807103640/https://ew.com/tv/2017/02/24/spoiler-room-arrow-shield-blacklist/ |archive-date=August 7, 2019 |access-date=August 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| significant_other  = [[Jemma Simmons]]; [[Aida (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Aida]]\n| first_date         = September 24, 2013\n}}\n'''Leopold James Fitz''' is a [[character (arts)|fictional character]] that originated in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] before appearing in [[Marvel Comics]]. The character, created by [[Joss Whedon]], [[Jed Whedon]] and [[Maurissa Tancharoen]], first appeared in the [[Pilot (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|pilot episode]] of ''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'' in 2013, and has continually been portrayed by [[Iain De Caestecker]].\n\nIn the series, Fitz is one of [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'s top scientific minds. His scientific knowledge is vast, and as an engineer and inventor has developed many of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s staple devices and gadgets. Many of his storylines involve his relationship with his best friend, and later lover, [[Jemma Simmons]]. Over the course of the series, Fitz suffers multiple traumas, and becomes aware of a darker and more ruthless side to his character.\n\n== Fictional character biography ==\nIn [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 1)|season one]], Leo Fitz is brought on to [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] agent [[Phil Coulson]]'s team as an engineering and weapons technology specialist.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Pilot |episode-link=Pilot (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=September 24, 2013 |season=1 |number=1}}</ref> He has a close bond with fellow agent [[Jemma Simmons]], who he met at the S.H.I.E.L.D. academy, with both being its Science and Technology division's youngest graduates.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/agents-shield-elizabeth-henstridge-1071757/ |title=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s Elizabeth Henstridge: Fitz and Simmons Are \"Like a Married Couple\" |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=October 7, 2013 |website=[[TV Guide]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190715070951/https://www.tvguide.com/news/agents-shield-elizabeth-henstridge-1071757/ |archive-date=July 15, 2019 |access-date=July 15, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.themarysue.com/agents-of-shield-recap-seeds/ |title=Agents of SHIELD Recap: \"Seeds\" |last=Polo |first=Susana |date=January 15, 2014 |website=[[The Mary Sue]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190715071124/https://www.themarysue.com/agents-of-shield-recap-seeds/ |archive-date=July 15, 2019 |access-date=July 15, 2019}}</ref> Near the end of the season, Fitz and Simmons lock themselves inside a medical unit for safety from rogue agent [[Grant Ward (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Grant Ward]], who ejects the unit into the ocean.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Ragtag |episode-link=Ragtag (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 6, 2014 |season=1 |number=21}}</ref> While trapped, Fitz professes his feelings for Simmons. Both are rescued by [[Nick Fury]], but Fitz sustains damage to his temporal lobe as a result of oxygen deprivation and is left comatose.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Beginning of the End |episode-link=Beginning of the End (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 13, 2014 |season=1 |number=22}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 2)|season two]], Fitz initially struggles with technology and speech as a result of Ward's actions,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Shadows |episode-link=Shadows (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=September 23, 2014 |season=2 |number=1}}</ref> but over time becomes a full member of the team again.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Face My Enemy |episode-link=Face My Enemy |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=October 14, 2014 |season=2 |number=4}}</ref> Near the end of the season, as Fitz arranges for a date with Simmons, a [[Kree]] weapon called the \"Monolith\", which is in S.H.I.E.L.D. custody, breaks free of containment and absorbs Simmons into itself.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=S.O.S., Part Two |episode-link=S.O.S. (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 12, 2015 |season=2 |number=22}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 3)|season three]], Fitz acquires an ancient [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]] scroll describing the Monolith that consumed Simmons as \"Death\" ({{lang-he|\u05de\u05d5\u05ea|link=no}}), which Fitz is unable to accept. Unknown to him, Simmons is alive on a desolate alien planet.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Laws of Nature |episode-link=Laws of Nature (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=September 29, 2015 |season=3 |number=1}}</ref> Fitz realizes that the Monolith is a portal, and with help from the [[Asgard (comics)|Asgardian]] Elliot Randolph and S.H.I.E.L.D. agent [[Daisy Johnson (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Daisy Johnson]], is able to enter the portal. He finds Simmons and is able to rescue her just as Daisy's power destroys the Monolith.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Purpose in the Machine |episode-link=Purpose in the Machine |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=October 6, 2015 |season=3 |number=2}}</ref> Simmons later tells Fitz about the six months she spent stranded on the desert planet.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=4,722 Hours |episode-link=4,722 Hours |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=October 27, 2015 |season=3 |number=5}}</ref> Fitz and Simmons eventually consummate their relationship.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Singularity |episode-link=The Singularity (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=April 26, 2016 |season=3 |number=18}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 4)|season four]], Fitz discovers that S.H.I.E.L.D. ally [[Holden Radcliffe (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Holden Radcliffe]] has created the android [[Aida (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Aida]], and agrees to help perfect her, while initially keeping this from Simmons.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Ghost |episode-link=The Ghost (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=September 20, 2016 |season=4 |number=1}}</ref> When Fitz's consciousness is submerged in the Framework, a [[virtual reality]] created by Radcliffe,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Self Control |episode-link=Self Control (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=February 21, 2017 |season=4 |number=15}}</ref> he becomes \"The Doctor\", [[Hydra (comics)|Hydra]]'s remorseless second-in-command, and has a relationship with Aida, who now goes by [[Madame Hydra|Ophelia / Madame Hydra]].<ref>{{Cite episode |title=What If... |episode-link=What If... (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=April 4, 2017 |season=4 |number=16}}</ref><ref name=\"Identity and Change\" /> After he creates for Aida a machine to become a real person, Fitz is forced out of the Framework,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Farewell, Cruel World! |episode-link=Farewell, Cruel World! |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 2, 2017 |season=4 |number=20}}</ref> and is traumatized from his behavior there. But when Aida learns Fitz does not love her back, she plans her revenge on him.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Return |episode-link=The Return (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 9, 2017 |season=4 |number=21}}</ref> S.H.I.E.L.D. eventually succeeds in defeating her. Shortly after, everyone in the team except Fitz are taken away by an unknown group.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=World's End |episode-link=World's End (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 16, 2017 |season=4 |number=22}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 5)|season five]], the team have been transported to a space station in the future, with only Fitz left behind.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Orientation, Part One |episode-link=Orientation (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=December 1, 2017 |season=5 |number=1}}</ref> Fitz is taken into military custody, but broken out six months later with [[Lance Hunter (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Lance Hunter]]'s help. [[Enoch (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Enoch]], a Chronicom, helps him escape to a secret bunker where Fitz learns that he was left behind so he could save the team. Aboard Enoch's ship, Fitz goes into [[Stasis (fiction)|stasis]] until Enoch awakens him 74 years later when they reach their destination.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Rewind |episode-link=Rewind (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=December 22, 2017 |season=5 |number=5}}</ref> After Fitz and the team return to the present,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=All the Comforts of Home |episode-link=All the Comforts of Home |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=March 2, 2018 |season=5 |number=11}}</ref> Fitz and Simmons marry in a ceremony organized by S.H.I.E.L.D.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Real Deal |episode-link=The Real Deal (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=March 9, 2018 |season=5 |number=12}}</ref> Due to multiple stressful factors, Fitz experiences a psychic split which enables his \"Doctor\" personality from the Framework to temporarily resurface.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Devil Complex |episode-link=The Devil Complex |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=March 23, 2018 |season=5 |number=14}}</ref> During the final battle against a gravitonium-enhanced [[Glenn Talbot (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Glenn Talbot]], Fitz is buried under a rubble and later found fatally injured when dug out by fellow agents [[Melinda May]] and [[Mack (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Mack]] where he succumbs to his wounds. Simmons resolves to find the present version of Fitz, who is in stasis aboard Enoch's ship.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The End |episode-link=The End (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 18, 2018 |season=5 |number=22}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 6)|season six]], as Daisy and Simmons lead the search for Fitz,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Missing Pieces |episode-link=Missing Pieces (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 10, 2019 |season=6 |number=1}}</ref> Enoch releases Fitz prematurely when they come under attack.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Window of Opportunity |episode-link=Window of Opportunity (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 17, 2019 |season=6 |number=2}}</ref> They reach the planet Kitson, where Fitz and Simmons reunite until the assassin Malachi makes off with Fitz.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Fear and Loathing on the Planet of Kitson |episode-link=Fear and Loathing on the Planet of Kitson |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 24, 2019 |season=6 |number=3}}</ref> For Fitz's safety, Simmons surrenders herself to Atarah, Enoch's former superior, so that the two of them can come up with a time-traveling method for the Chronicoms to use.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Other Thing |episode-link=The Other Thing |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=June 14, 2019 |season=6 |number=5}}</ref> Atarah traps Fitz and Simmons inside their own minds, forcing them to work together in figuring out time travel logic. The duo are ultimately freed by Enoch, who manages to overpower Atarah and her forces. The trio then teleport away,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Inescapable |episode-link=Inescapable (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=June 21, 2019 |season=6 |number=6}}</ref> but end up again on Kitson, where Fitz and Simmons are saved from execution by mercenary [[Izel (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Izel]], who helps them on their return to Earth while Enoch bids them farewell.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Toldja |episode-link=Toldja |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=June 28, 2019 |season=6 |number=7}}</ref> Izel believes Fitz and Simmons are conspiring against her, so she commands her ship's crew to eliminate them. The two are ultimately rescued by a team led by Mack, and return to Earth.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Collision Course (Part II) |episode-link=Collision Course (Part II) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=July 12, 2019 |season=6 |number=9}}</ref> While S.H.I.E.L.D stops Izel, Fitz and Simmons are ambushed by the Chronicom Hunters, but saved by Enoch who helps them achieve time travel as well as create a Coulson [[Life Model Decoy|LMD]] to help them fight the Hunters.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=New Life |episode-link=New Life (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=August 2, 2019 |season=6 |number=13}}</ref>\n\n== Concept and creation ==\n[[Iain De Caestecker]] was cast as Leo Fitz in November 2012.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/elizabeth-henstridge-iain-de-caestecker-shield-joss-whedon-389604 |title=Joss Whedon's 'S.H.I.E.L.D.' Pilot Adds Two Agents (Exclusive) |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |date=November 13, 2012 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6C9JCJpva?url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/elizabeth-henstridge-iain-de-caestecker-shield-joss-whedon-389604 |archive-date=November 13, 2012}}</ref> Following injuries the character receives at the end of the first season, the series began to deal with brain trauma, as De Caestecker explained \"From the get-go, before I even knew about it, the writers had the idea, and they did a lot of research in it with doctors. When I found out about it, I did my own research and correlated it together. It's just something that should never be trivialized. It's a real and serious thing to a lot of people, brain trauma, so we just have to constantly be respectful towards it. We talk about it all the time. Even if you don't see it or it's not obvious, it's always something that's in our heads that we're keeping going. It's the realization that you never get fully better, it's about embracing the new side of you and making that work in the world that you're in. I suppose the idea of a cure\u2014I don't know if that could happen.\"<ref name=\"HenstridgeDeCaesteckerS2\" /> For Fitz's costume design, Foley tried to have his clothes reflect his personality, without \"getting too clich\u00e9...we try and play up his \"heritage style\"...using classic design details on him like paisley & leather elbow patches and mixing them with different plaids.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tyrannyofstyle.com/agents-of-shield-costume-design |title=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. Costume Design |last=Kucharski |first=Joe |date=December 19, 2013 |website=Tyranny of Style |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6Tbqq0bZl?url=http://tyrannyofstyle.com/agents-of-shield-costume-design |archive-date=October 26, 2014 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Characterization ==\nDe Caestecker, in describing the character, said that \"Fitz has got this funny kind of temper. He's quite passionate about what he does. So those moments where\u2014I don't think he's someone that really responds very quickly to emotion; he doesn't really understand emotions as much\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://shieldsite.net/s-h-i-e-l-d-on-set-iain-de-caestecker-on-character-development-sif-a-monkey-for-fitz/21186 |title=S.H.I.E.L.D. On Set: Iain de Caestecker On Character Development, Sif & A Monkey For Fitz |last=Byrne |first=Craig |date=February 2, 2014 |website=SHIELD.SITE |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6SY6lSfJp?url=http://shieldsite.net/s-h-i-e-l-d-on-set-iain-de-caestecker-on-character-development-sif-a-monkey-for-fitz/21186 |archive-date=September 13, 2014 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref> Fitz has a lot of interaction with Simmons in the series, with De Caestecker explaining \"My character, he's Engineering, so he's on the computer and tech side of everything. He's consumed within that world, and he works very closely with Simmons, who's Biochem. They\u2019ve got this kind of weird chemistry together, and they just kind of fit each other in a very weird way.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://au.ign.com/articles/2013/07/17/marvels-agents-of-shield-iain-de-caestecker-on-agent-leo-fitz |title=Marvel's Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.: Iain De Caestecker on Agent Leo Fitz |last=Goldman |first=Eric |date=July 16, 2013 |website=[[IGN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6SY6rR6sr?url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/07/17/marvels-agents-of-shield-iain-de-caestecker-on-agent-leo-fitz |archive-date=September 13, 2014 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref> Regarding the changing dynamic over time between Fitz and Simmons, De Caestecker said \"I suppose what's happened from the start of season two up to midseason is, they've become a lot stronger as individuals, I think. But I think they still care for and need each other a lot, and they also work better together when they are together. But I think there's a lot of things that have still been unsaid and will hopefully come out, certain confrontations that are still bubbling under.\"<ref name=\"HenstridgeDeCaesteckerS2\" /> Fitz also develops a close friendship with [[Mack (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Alphonso \"Mack\" MacKenzie]], beginning when the latter joins the cast in season two.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://comics2film.com/marvel-s-agents-of-s-h-i-e-l-d-fitz-mack-s-bromance |title=Marvel's Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. {{!}} Fitz + Mack's Bromance |date=July 31, 2019 |website=Comics2Film |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812161246/https://comics2film.com/marvel-s-agents-of-s-h-i-e-l-d-fitz-mack-s-bromance |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |access-date=August 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\nReviewing the season 1 episode \"[[0-8-4]]\", Eric Goldman of [[IGN]] criticized the lack of development for the majority of main characters, specifically Fitz and Simmons as he did with the pilot episode.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/02/marvels-agents-of-shield-0-8-4-review |title=Marvel's Agents of SHIELD: \"0-8-4\" Review |last=Goldman |first=Eric |date=October 1, 2013 |website=[[IGN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190705045911/https://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/02/marvels-agents-of-shield-0-8-4-review |archive-date=July 5, 2019 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref> However, he was more positive while reviewing \"[[FZZT]]\", praising it for finally giving the \"well-needed\" development of them both.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2013/11/06/marvels-agents-of-shield-fzzt-review |title=Marvel's Agents of SHIELD: \"F.Z.Z.T.\" Review |last=Goldman |first=Eric |date=5 November 2013 |website=[[IGN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190705051319/https://www.ign.com/articles/2013/11/06/marvels-agents-of-shield-fzzt-review |archive-date=July 5, 2019 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref> De Caestecker was named [[TVLine]]'s \"Performer of the Week\" for the week of September 27, 2015, for his performance in \"[[Laws of Nature (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Laws of Nature]]\", particularly the episode's final scene.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2015/10/03/iain-de-caestecker-performance-agents-of-shield-season-3/ |title=Performer of the Week: S.H.I.E.L.D.'s Iain De Caestecker |date=October 3, 2015 |website=[[TVLine]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6c2PnuH9P?url=http://tvline.com/2015/10/03/iain-de-caestecker-performance-agents-of-shield-season-3/ |archive-date=October 4, 2015 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Other appearances ==\n=== Comics ===\nFitz made his [[Marvel Comics]] debut in ''S.H.I.E.L.D.'' (Vol. 3) #1 (February 2015) by [[Mark Waid]] and [[Carlos Pacheco]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbr.com/characters-debuted-on-tv/ |title=16 Characters You Never Knew Debuted On Screen First |last=Curovic |first=Irina |date=October 15, 2017 |website=[[CBR.com|CBR]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190706103154/https://www.cbr.com/characters-debuted-on-tv/ |archive-date=July 6, 2019 |access-date=July 6, 2019}}</ref> He joins Phil Coulson's team to regain the Uru Sword, an ancient weapon that belonged to [[Heimdall (comics)|Heimdall]]. He contacted the [[Vision (Marvel Comics)|Vision]] in helping Heimdall overcome an alien rock that was possessing him. Fitz then delivered the rock to be analyzed by Jemma Simmons.\n\nHis next assignment was protecting [[Wiccan (comics)|Wiccan]] from a man who had special bullets that could harm magic users. With [[Scarlet Witch]]'s help, the team traveled to [[Antarctica]] to find the source and managed to defeat the people who were making the bullets. However, [[Dormammu]] took possession of Fitz and shot Scarlet Witch. After Dormammu was defeated, Fitz regained his senses.<ref>S.H.I.E.L.D. Vol. 3 #5</ref>\n\nHe became part of an elaborate plan by Coulson to retrieve the Quantum Drive from [[Hydra (comics)|Hydra agents]].<ref>Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. #4</ref> Afterwards, [[Maria Hill]] began to suspect that there was a traitor in their midst and hired [[Elektra (character)|Elektra]] to sniff him out. Because Coulson was absent, Fitz could not be safeguarded by him and was forced to flee when Elektra accused him of being the traitor. He meets up with Coulson, who is taken back to [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] by Elektra, and escapes with [[Daisy Johnson|Quake]].<ref>Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. #9</ref> Together they out the Department of Defence's General Strakovsky as the traitor and Fitz, along with Coulson and Quake, are reinstated at S.H.I.E.L.D.<ref>Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. #10</ref>\n\n=== Web series ===\nLeo Fitz appears in the digital series ''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.: Slingshot]]'' with Iain De Caestecker reprising his role.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/watch-the-full-marvels-agents-of-shield-slingshot-spinoff-series-here |title=Watch the full Marvel's Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.: Slingshot spinoff series HERE |last=Caron |first=Nathalie |date=2016-12-13 |website=[[Syfy Wire]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190423203832/https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/watch-the-full-marvels-agents-of-shield-slingshot-spinoff-series-here |archive-date=April 23, 2019 |access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n\n=== Video games ===\nFitz is a playable DLC character in ''[[Lego Marvel's Avengers]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://themarvelreport.com/2016/05/lego-avengers-agents-shield-dlc-review/ |title=Lego Avengers Agents of SHIELD DLC Review |last=Richter |first=Shawn |date=May 18, 2016 |website=The Marvel Report |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181122161437/http://themarvelreport.com/2016/05/lego-avengers-agents-shield-dlc-review/ |archive-date=November 22, 2018 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Animation ===\nFitz, voiced by De Caestecker, appeared in \"Lizards\" a fourth season episode of the animated TV series ''[[Ultimate Spider-Man (TV series)|Ultimate Spider-Man]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/ultimate-spider-man-shield-fitz-simmons-clip/ |title=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. Characters Join Ultimate Spider-Man Cartoon |last=Chipman |first=Bob |date=March 9, 2016 |website=[[Screen Rant]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705044405/https://screenrant.com/ultimate-spider-man-shield-fitz-simmons-clip/ |archive-date=July 5, 2019 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/sneak-peek-39-agents-of-s-1382276190830646.html |title=Sneak Peek: 'Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.' Lends FitzSimmons to 'Ultimate Spider-Man' |last=Chan |first=Robert |date=March 10, 2016 |website=[[Yahoo!]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190730131235/https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/sneak-peek-39-agents-of-s-1382276190830646.html |archive-date=July 30, 2019 |access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"HenstridgeDeCaesteckerS2\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/agents-of-shields-henstridge-caestecker-on-the-future-of-fitzsimmons |title=\"Agents of SHIELD's\" Henstridge & Caestecker on the Future of FitzSimmons |last=Huver |first=Scott |date=March 24, 2015 |website=CBR.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6YaDnETF4?url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/agents-of-shields-henstridge-caestecker-on-the-future-of-fitzsimmons |archive-date=May 17, 2015 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Marveldatabase}}\n\n{{S.H.I.E.L.D.}}\n{{Marvel Cinematic Universe|selected=Cast}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fitz, Leo}}\n\n[[Category:Fictional characters with multiple personalities]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters with posttraumatic stress disorder]]\n[[Category:Fictional computer scientists]]\n[[Category:Fictional dictators]]\n[[Category:Fictional electronic engineers]]\n[[Category:Fictional immigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Fictional inventors]]\n[[Category:Fictional mad scientists]]\n[[Category:Fictional murderers]]\n[[Category:Fictional roboticists]]\n[[Category:Fictional Scottish people]]\n[[Category:Fictional torturers and interrogators]]\n[[Category:Fictional victims of brainwashing and indoctrination]]\n[[Category:Male characters in television]]\n[[Category:Marvel Cinematic Universe specific characters]]\n[[Category:S.H.I.E.L.D. agents]]\n[[Category:Television characters introduced in 2013]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. character}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox character\n| color              = #AF181F\n| name               = Leo Fitz\n| series             = {{no italics|[[Marvel Cinematic Universe]]}}\n| image              = Leo Fitz.jpg\n| caption            = Iain De Caestecker as Leo Fitz in a promotional image for [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 4)|season four]]\n| first_minor        = [[Pilot (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Pilot]]\n| creator            = {{plainlist|\n* [[Joss Whedon]]\n* [[Jed Whedon]]\n* [[Maurissa Tancharoen]]\n}}\n| portrayer          = [[Iain De Caestecker]]\n| full_name          = Leopold James Fitz<ref name=\"Identity and Change\">{{Cite episode |title=Identity and Change |episode-link=Identity and Change (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=April 11, 2017 |season=4 |number=17 |quote='''Simmons:''' It's complicated, but I know him, not as the Doctor, but as {{sic|a a}} brilliant, awkward, heroic scientist named Leopold James Fitz.}}</ref>\n| alias              = The Doctor\n| occupation         = Engineer<br />[[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] agent\n| nationality        = Scottish<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ew.com/tv/2017/02/24/spoiler-room-arrow-shield-blacklist/ |title=Spoiler Room: Scoop on 'Arrow,' 'Agents of SHIELD,' 'Blacklist,' more |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=24 February 2017 |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190807103640/https://ew.com/tv/2017/02/24/spoiler-room-arrow-shield-blacklist/ |archive-date=August 7, 2019 |access-date=August 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| significant_other  = [[Jemma Simmons]]; [[Aida (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Aida]]\n| first_date         = September 24, 2013\n}}\n'''Leopold James Fitz''' is a [[character (arts)|fictional character]] that originated in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] before appearing in [[Marvel Comics]]. The character, created by [[Joss Whedon]], [[Jed Whedon]] and [[Maurissa Tancharoen]], first appeared in the [[Pilot (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|pilot episode]] of ''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'' in 2013, and has continually been portrayed by [[Iain De Caestecker]].\n\nIn the series, Fitz is one of [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'s top scientific minds. His scientific knowledge is vast, and as an engineer and inventor has developed many of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s staple devices and gadgets. Many of his storylines involve his relationship with his best friend, and later lover, [[Jemma Simmons]]. Over the course of the series, Fitz suffers multiple traumas, and becomes aware of a darker and more ruthless side to his character.\n\n== Fictional character biography ==\nIn [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 1)|season one]], Leo Fitz is brought on to [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] agent [[Phil Coulson]]'s team as an engineering and weapons technology specialist.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Pilot |episode-link=Pilot (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=September 24, 2013 |season=1 |number=1}}</ref> He has a close bond with fellow agent [[Jemma Simmons]], who he met at the S.H.I.E.L.D. academy, with both being its Science and Technology division's youngest graduates.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/agents-shield-elizabeth-henstridge-1071757/ |title=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s Elizabeth Henstridge: Fitz and Simmons Are \"Like a Married Couple\" |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=October 7, 2013 |website=[[TV Guide]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190715070951/https://www.tvguide.com/news/agents-shield-elizabeth-henstridge-1071757/ |archive-date=July 15, 2019 |access-date=July 15, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.themarysue.com/agents-of-shield-recap-seeds/ |title=Agents of SHIELD Recap: \"Seeds\" |last=Polo |first=Susana |date=January 15, 2014 |website=[[The Mary Sue]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190715071124/https://www.themarysue.com/agents-of-shield-recap-seeds/ |archive-date=July 15, 2019 |access-date=July 15, 2019}}</ref> Near the end of the season, Fitz and Simmons lock themselves inside a medical unit for safety from rogue agent [[Grant Ward (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Grant Ward]], who ejects the unit into the ocean.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Ragtag |episode-link=Ragtag (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 6, 2014 |season=1 |number=21}}</ref> While trapped, Fitz professes his feelings for Simmons. Both are rescued by [[Nick Fury]], but Fitz sustains damage to his temporal lobe as a result of oxygen deprivation and is left comatose.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Beginning of the End |episode-link=Beginning of the End (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 13, 2014 |season=1 |number=22}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 2)|season two]], Fitz initially struggles with technology and speech as a result of Ward's actions,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Shadows |episode-link=Shadows (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=September 23, 2014 |season=2 |number=1}}</ref> but over time becomes a full member of the team again.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Face My Enemy |episode-link=Face My Enemy |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=October 14, 2014 |season=2 |number=4}}</ref> Near the end of the season, as Fitz arranges for a date with Simmons, a [[Kree]] weapon called the \"Monolith\", which is in S.H.I.E.L.D. custody, breaks free of containment and absorbs Simmons into itself.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=S.O.S., Part Two |episode-link=S.O.S. (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 12, 2015 |season=2 |number=22}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 3)|season three]], Fitz acquires an ancient [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]] scroll describing the Monolith that consumed Simmons as \"Death\" ({{lang-he|\u05de\u05d5\u05ea|link=no}}), which Fitz is unable to accept. Unknown to him, Simmons is alive on a desolate alien planet.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Laws of Nature |episode-link=Laws of Nature (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=September 29, 2015 |season=3 |number=1}}</ref> Fitz realizes that the Monolith is a portal, and with help from the [[Asgard (comics)|Asgardian]] Elliot Randolph and S.H.I.E.L.D. agent [[Daisy Johnson (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Daisy Johnson]], is able to enter the portal. He finds Simmons and is able to rescue her just as Daisy's power destroys the Monolith.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Purpose in the Machine |episode-link=Purpose in the Machine |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=October 6, 2015 |season=3 |number=2}}</ref> Simmons later tells Fitz about the six months she spent stranded on the desert planet.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=4,722 Hours |episode-link=4,722 Hours |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=October 27, 2015 |season=3 |number=5}}</ref> Fitz and Simmons eventually consummate their relationship.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Singularity |episode-link=The Singularity (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=April 26, 2016 |season=3 |number=18}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 4)|season four]], Fitz discovers that S.H.I.E.L.D. ally [[Holden Radcliffe (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Holden Radcliffe]] has created the android [[Aida (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Aida]], and agrees to help perfect her, while initially keeping this from Simmons.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Ghost |episode-link=The Ghost (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=September 20, 2016 |season=4 |number=1}}</ref> When Fitz's consciousness is submerged in the Framework, a [[virtual reality]] created by Radcliffe,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Self Control |episode-link=Self Control (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=February 21, 2017 |season=4 |number=15}}</ref> he becomes \"The Doctor\", [[Hydra (comics)|Hydra]]'s remorseless second-in-command, and has a relationship with Aida, who now goes by [[Madame Hydra|Ophelia / Madame Hydra]].<ref>{{Cite episode |title=What If... |episode-link=What If... (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=April 4, 2017 |season=4 |number=16}}</ref><ref name=\"Identity and Change\" /> After he creates for Aida a machine to become a real person, Fitz is forced out of the Framework,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Farewell, Cruel World! |episode-link=Farewell, Cruel World! |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 2, 2017 |season=4 |number=20}}</ref> and is traumatized from his behavior there. But when Aida learns Fitz does not love her back, she plans her revenge on him.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Return |episode-link=The Return (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 9, 2017 |season=4 |number=21}}</ref> S.H.I.E.L.D. eventually succeeds in defeating her. Shortly after, everyone in the team except Fitz are taken away by an unknown group.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=World's End |episode-link=World's End (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 16, 2017 |season=4 |number=22}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 5)|season five]], the team have been transported to a space station in the future, with only Fitz left behind.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Orientation, Part One |episode-link=Orientation (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=December 1, 2017 |season=5 |number=1}}</ref> Fitz is taken into military custody, but broken out six months later with [[Lance Hunter (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Lance Hunter]]'s help. [[Enoch (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Enoch]], a Chronicom, helps him escape to a secret bunker where Fitz learns that he was left behind so he could save the team. Aboard Enoch's ship, Fitz goes into [[Stasis (fiction)|stasis]] until Enoch awakens him 74 years later when they reach their destination.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Rewind |episode-link=Rewind (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=December 22, 2017 |season=5 |number=5}}</ref> After Fitz and the team return to the present,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=All the Comforts of Home |episode-link=All the Comforts of Home |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=March 2, 2018 |season=5 |number=11}}</ref> Fitz and Simmons marry in a ceremony organized by S.H.I.E.L.D.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Real Deal |episode-link=The Real Deal (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=March 9, 2018 |season=5 |number=12}}</ref> Due to multiple stressful factors, Fitz experiences a psychic split which enables his \"Doctor\" personality from the Framework to temporarily resurface.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Devil Complex |episode-link=The Devil Complex |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=March 23, 2018 |season=5 |number=14}}</ref> During the final battle against a gravitonium-enhanced [[Glenn Talbot (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Glenn Talbot]], Fitz is buried under a rubble and later found fatally injured when dug out by fellow agents [[Melinda May]] and [[Mack (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Mack]] where he succumbs to his wounds. Simmons resolves to find the present version of Fitz, who is in stasis aboard Enoch's ship.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The End |episode-link=The End (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 18, 2018 |season=5 |number=22}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 6)|season six]], as Daisy and Simmons lead the search for Fitz,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Missing Pieces |episode-link=Missing Pieces (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 10, 2019 |season=6 |number=1}}</ref> Enoch releases Fitz prematurely when they come under attack.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Window of Opportunity |episode-link=Window of Opportunity (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 17, 2019 |season=6 |number=2}}</ref> They reach the planet Kitson, where Fitz and Simmons reunite until the assassin Malachi makes off with Fitz.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Fear and Loathing on the Planet of Kitson |episode-link=Fear and Loathing on the Planet of Kitson |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=May 24, 2019 |season=6 |number=3}}</ref> For Fitz's safety, Simmons surrenders herself to Atarah, Enoch's former superior, so that the two of them can come up with a time-traveling method for the Chronicoms to use.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=The Other Thing |episode-link=The Other Thing |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=June 14, 2019 |season=6 |number=5}}</ref> Atarah traps Fitz and Simmons inside their own minds, forcing them to work together in figuring out time travel logic. The duo are ultimately freed by Enoch, who manages to overpower Atarah and her forces. The trio then teleport away,<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Inescapable |episode-link=Inescapable (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=June 21, 2019 |season=6 |number=6}}</ref> but end up again on Kitson, where Fitz and Simmons are saved from execution by mercenary [[Izel (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Izel]], who helps them on their return to Earth while Enoch bids them farewell.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Toldja |episode-link=Toldja |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=June 28, 2019 |season=6 |number=7}}</ref> Izel believes Fitz and Simmons are conspiring against her, so she commands her ship's crew to eliminate them. The two are ultimately rescued by a team led by Mack, and return to Earth.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Collision Course (Part II) |episode-link=Collision Course (Part II) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=July 12, 2019 |season=6 |number=9}}</ref> While S.H.I.E.L.D stops Izel, Fitz and Simmons are ambushed by the Chronicom Hunters, but saved by Enoch who helps them achieve time travel as well as create a Coulson [[Life Model Decoy|LMD]] to help them fight the Hunters.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=New Life |episode-link=New Life (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.) |series=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |series-link=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. |network=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=August 2, 2019 |season=6 |number=13}}</ref>\n\n== Concept and creation ==\n[[Iain De Caestecker]] was cast as Leo Fitz in November 2012.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/elizabeth-henstridge-iain-de-caestecker-shield-joss-whedon-389604 |title=Joss Whedon's 'S.H.I.E.L.D.' Pilot Adds Two Agents (Exclusive) |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |date=November 13, 2012 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=5 July 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6C9JCJpva?url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/elizabeth-henstridge-iain-de-caestecker-shield-joss-whedon-389604 |archive-date=November 13, 2012}}</ref> Following injuries the character receives at the end of the first season, the series began to deal with brain trauma, as De Caestecker explained \"From the get-go, before I even knew about it, the writers had the idea, and they did a lot of research in it with doctors. When I found out about it, I did my own research and correlated it together. It's just something that should never be trivialized. It's a real and serious thing to a lot of people, brain trauma, so we just have to constantly be respectful towards it. We talk about it all the time. Even if you don't see it or it's not obvious, it's always something that's in our heads that we're keeping going. It's the realization that you never get fully better, it's about embracing the new side of you and making that work in the world that you're in. I suppose the idea of a cure\u2014I don't know if that could happen.\"<ref name=\"HenstridgeDeCaesteckerS2\" /> For Fitz's costume design, Foley tried to have his clothes reflect his personality, without \"getting too clich\u00e9...we try and play up his \"heritage style\"...using classic design details on him like paisley & leather elbow patches and mixing them with different plaids.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tyrannyofstyle.com/agents-of-shield-costume-design |title=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. Costume Design |last=Kucharski |first=Joe |date=December 19, 2013 |website=Tyranny of Style |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6Tbqq0bZl?url=http://tyrannyofstyle.com/agents-of-shield-costume-design |archive-date=October 26, 2014 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Characterization ==\nDe Caestecker, in describing the character, said that \"Fitz has got this funny kind of temper. He's quite passionate about what he does. So those moments where\u2014I don't think he's someone that really responds very quickly to emotion; he doesn't really understand emotions as much\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://shieldsite.net/s-h-i-e-l-d-on-set-iain-de-caestecker-on-character-development-sif-a-monkey-for-fitz/21186 |title=S.H.I.E.L.D. On Set: Iain de Caestecker On Character Development, Sif & A Monkey For Fitz |last=Byrne |first=Craig |date=February 2, 2014 |website=SHIELD.SITE |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6SY6lSfJp?url=http://shieldsite.net/s-h-i-e-l-d-on-set-iain-de-caestecker-on-character-development-sif-a-monkey-for-fitz/21186 |archive-date=September 13, 2014 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref> Fitz has a lot of interaction with Simmons in the series, with De Caestecker explaining \"My character, he's Engineering, so he's on the computer and tech side of everything. He's consumed within that world, and he works very closely with Simmons, who's Biochem. They\u2019ve got this kind of weird chemistry together, and they just kind of fit each other in a very weird way.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://au.ign.com/articles/2013/07/17/marvels-agents-of-shield-iain-de-caestecker-on-agent-leo-fitz |title=Marvel's Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.: Iain De Caestecker on Agent Leo Fitz |last=Goldman |first=Eric |date=July 16, 2013 |website=[[IGN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6SY6rR6sr?url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/07/17/marvels-agents-of-shield-iain-de-caestecker-on-agent-leo-fitz |archive-date=September 13, 2014 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref> Regarding the changing dynamic over time between Fitz and Simmons, De Caestecker said \"I suppose what's happened from the start of season two up to midseason is, they've become a lot stronger as individuals, I think. But I think they still care for and need each other a lot, and they also work better together when they are together. But I think there's a lot of things that have still been unsaid and will hopefully come out, certain confrontations that are still bubbling under.\"<ref name=\"HenstridgeDeCaesteckerS2\" /> Fitz also develops a close friendship with [[Mack (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Alphonso \"Mack\" MacKenzie]], beginning when the latter joins the cast in season two.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://comics2film.com/marvel-s-agents-of-s-h-i-e-l-d-fitz-mack-s-bromance |title=Marvel's Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. {{!}} Fitz + Mack's Bromance |date=July 31, 2019 |website=Comics2Film |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812161246/https://comics2film.com/marvel-s-agents-of-s-h-i-e-l-d-fitz-mack-s-bromance |archive-date=August 12, 2019 |access-date=August 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\nReviewing the season 1 episode \"[[0-8-4]]\", Eric Goldman of [[IGN]] criticized the lack of development for the majority of main characters, specifically Fitz and Simmons as he did with the pilot episode.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/02/marvels-agents-of-shield-0-8-4-review |title=Marvel's Agents of SHIELD: \"0-8-4\" Review |last=Goldman |first=Eric |date=October 1, 2013 |website=[[IGN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190705045911/https://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/02/marvels-agents-of-shield-0-8-4-review |archive-date=July 5, 2019 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref> However, he was more positive while reviewing \"[[FZZT]]\", praising it for finally giving the \"well-needed\" development of them both.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2013/11/06/marvels-agents-of-shield-fzzt-review |title=Marvel's Agents of SHIELD: \"F.Z.Z.T.\" Review |last=Goldman |first=Eric |date=5 November 2013 |website=[[IGN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190705051319/https://www.ign.com/articles/2013/11/06/marvels-agents-of-shield-fzzt-review |archive-date=July 5, 2019 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref> De Caestecker was named [[TVLine]]'s \"Performer of the Week\" for the week of September 27, 2015, for his performance in \"[[Laws of Nature (Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.)|Laws of Nature]]\", particularly the episode's final scene.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2015/10/03/iain-de-caestecker-performance-agents-of-shield-season-3/ |title=Performer of the Week: S.H.I.E.L.D.'s Iain De Caestecker |date=October 3, 2015 |website=[[TVLine]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6c2PnuH9P?url=http://tvline.com/2015/10/03/iain-de-caestecker-performance-agents-of-shield-season-3/ |archive-date=October 4, 2015 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Other appearances ==\n=== Comics ===\nFitz made his [[Marvel Comics]] debut in ''S.H.I.E.L.D.'' (Vol. 3) #1 (February 2015) by [[Mark Waid]] and [[Carlos Pacheco]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cbr.com/characters-debuted-on-tv/ |title=16 Characters You Never Knew Debuted On Screen First |last=Curovic |first=Irina |date=October 15, 2017 |website=[[CBR.com|CBR]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190706103154/https://www.cbr.com/characters-debuted-on-tv/ |archive-date=July 6, 2019 |access-date=July 6, 2019}}</ref> He joins Phil Coulson's team to regain the Uru Sword, an ancient weapon that belonged to [[Heimdall (comics)|Heimdall]]. He contacted the [[Vision (Marvel Comics)|Vision]] in helping Heimdall overcome an alien rock that was possessing him. Fitz then delivered the rock to be analyzed by Jemma Simmons.\n\nHis next assignment was protecting [[Wiccan (comics)|Wiccan]] from a man who had special bullets that could harm magic users. With [[Scarlet Witch]]'s help, the team traveled to [[Antarctica]] to find the source and managed to defeat the people who were making the bullets. However, [[Dormammu]] took possession of Fitz and shot Scarlet Witch. After Dormammu was defeated, Fitz regained his senses.<ref>S.H.I.E.L.D. Vol. 3 #5</ref>\n\nHe became part of an elaborate plan by Coulson to retrieve the Quantum Drive from [[Hydra (comics)|Hydra agents]].<ref>Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. #4</ref> Afterwards, [[Maria Hill]] began to suspect that there was a traitor in their midst and hired [[Elektra (character)|Elektra]] to sniff him out. Because Coulson was absent, Fitz could not be safeguarded by him and was forced to flee when Elektra accused him of being the traitor. He meets up with Coulson, who is taken back to [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] by Elektra, and escapes with [[Daisy Johnson|Quake]].<ref>Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. #9</ref> Together they out the Department of Defence's General Strakovsky as the traitor and Fitz, along with Coulson and Quake, are reinstated at S.H.I.E.L.D.<ref>Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. #10</ref>\n\n=== Web series ===\nLeo Fitz appears in the digital series ''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.: Slingshot]]'' with Iain De Caestecker reprising his role.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/watch-the-full-marvels-agents-of-shield-slingshot-spinoff-series-here |title=Watch the full Marvel's Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.: Slingshot spinoff series HERE |last=Caron |first=Nathalie |date=2016-12-13 |website=[[Syfy Wire]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190423203832/https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/watch-the-full-marvels-agents-of-shield-slingshot-spinoff-series-here |archive-date=April 23, 2019 |access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n\n=== Video games ===\nFitz is a playable DLC character in ''[[Lego Marvel's Avengers]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://themarvelreport.com/2016/05/lego-avengers-agents-shield-dlc-review/ |title=Lego Avengers Agents of SHIELD DLC Review |last=Richter |first=Shawn |date=May 18, 2016 |website=The Marvel Report |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181122161437/http://themarvelreport.com/2016/05/lego-avengers-agents-shield-dlc-review/ |archive-date=November 22, 2018 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Animation ===\nFitz, voiced by De Caestecker, appeared in \"Lizards\" a fourth season episode of the animated TV series ''[[Ultimate Spider-Man (TV series)|Ultimate Spider-Man]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/ultimate-spider-man-shield-fitz-simmons-clip/ |title=Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. Characters Join Ultimate Spider-Man Cartoon |last=Chipman |first=Bob |date=March 9, 2016 |website=[[Screen Rant]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705044405/https://screenrant.com/ultimate-spider-man-shield-fitz-simmons-clip/ |archive-date=July 5, 2019 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/sneak-peek-39-agents-of-s-1382276190830646.html |title=Sneak Peek: 'Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.' Lends FitzSimmons to 'Ultimate Spider-Man' |last=Chan |first=Robert |date=March 10, 2016 |website=[[Yahoo!]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190730131235/https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/sneak-peek-39-agents-of-s-1382276190830646.html |archive-date=July 30, 2019 |access-date=2019-08-01}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"HenstridgeDeCaesteckerS2\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/agents-of-shields-henstridge-caestecker-on-the-future-of-fitzsimmons |title=\"Agents of SHIELD's\" Henstridge & Caestecker on the Future of FitzSimmons |last=Huver |first=Scott |date=March 24, 2015 |website=CBR.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6YaDnETF4?url=http://www.comicbookresources.com/article/agents-of-shields-henstridge-caestecker-on-the-future-of-fitzsimmons |archive-date=May 17, 2015 |access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Marveldatabase}}\n\n{{S.H.I.E.L.D.}}\n{{Marvel Cinematic Universe}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fitz, Leo}}\n\n[[Category:Fictional characters with multiple personalities]]