ard, David R. ''The American Army and the First World War'' (Cambridge University Press, 2014). 484 pp. [http://www.h-net.org/reviews/showpdf.php?id=42718 online review]\n* {{cite book |title=Borrowed Soldiers: Americans under British Command, 1918 |first=Mitchell A. |last=Yockelson |authorlink = Mitchell Yockelson |others=Foreword by John S. D. Eisenhower |publisher=University of Oklahoma Press |year=2008| isbn=978-0-8061-3919-7}}\n* [[Yockelson, Mitchell]]. ''Forty-Seven Days: How Pershing's Warriors Came of Age to Defeat at the German Army in World War I'' (New York: NAL, Caliber, 2016) {{ISBN|978-0-451-46695-2}}\n* {{ACMH}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q272383|c=Category:John J. Pershing|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|m=no|mw=no|species=no|wikt=no|s=Author:John Joseph Pershing}}\n* [http://www.pershingmuseum.com Pershing Museum]\n* [http://www.arlingtoncemetery.net/johnjose.htm Biography of John J. Pershing]\n* [https://www.nytimes.com/learning/general/onthisday/bday/0913.html ''New York Times'' obituary]\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=John J. Pershing}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20031010072443/http://www.armyhistoryfnd.org/armyhist/research/detail2.cfm?webpage_id=117&page_type_id=3 Black Jack Pershing in Cuba]\n* [http://www.history.army.mil/books/Last_Salute/Ch4.htm CHAPTER IV, General of the Armies John J. Pershing, State Funeral, 15\u201319 July 1948] in [http://www.history.army.mil/books/Last_Salute/index.htm The Last Salute: Civil and Military Funeral, 1921\u20131969] by B.&nbsp;C.&nbsp;Mossman and M.&nbsp;W.&nbsp;Stark, [[United States Army Center of Military History]]\n* [http://www.nebraskahistory.org/lib-arch/research/manuscripts/family/pershing.htm John J. Pershing collection] at [[Nebraska State Historical Society]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150923193815/http://www.borrowedsoldiers.com/commanders/pershing.html Americans Under British Command, 1918] at Borrowed Soldiers\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=gov.dod.dimoc.30117|name=\